Paper: hep-th/9301071

Date: 1993-01-18

Title: Second Order Formalism for Fermions

Authors: J. L. Cort\'es, J. Gamboa and L. Vel\'azquez

Comments: 13 pp, Plain TeX, IPNO-TH 92/82, DFTUZ 92/13

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B313 (1993) 108-114

A new formulation of fermions based on a second order action is proposed. Ananalysis of the $U(1)$ anomaly allows us to test the validity of the formalismat the quantum level. This formulation gives a new perpective to theintroduction of parity non-invariant interactions.